dings><font color=151b54>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/uvaljeanesbdk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valjeanesbdk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brother of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#330000>(1/1/02 7:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The larger Scheme</span><hr size=1> For many months Khaldorn (veteran, but unrecognized barbarian warrior) have been sharing his experience with his 2 new companions Canute and Cogito. On this particular day he has taken the group as far away from home as Rathe Mntns. The objective: to familiarize his companions with the lands of Norrath. Currently he is explaining how best to defeat a hill giant in battle, noting however, that it will be a long time till they will need that knowledge rather than the trusty sow spell. having most of the afternoon studied a brave band of adventurers fighting a giant, and having now eaten a good meal. The party is preparing to make camp, out of sight from most beings. The evening is uneventful. But shortly after midnight, Khaldorn awakens with a queasy feeling in the pit of his stomach. He knows this feeling well. It is a sign if danger...evil is near. Knowing that his young companions would be more trouble than use, he sets out alone in the direction that he feels is the right. Having used a special barbarian mixture of grease and some secret ingredients on his armor, he can move very silently....for a barbarian.<br>
He closes in of a small forest, slowly, looking for any clues as to what the danger is. The queasy feeling turns into a hard knot and without a sound, he pulls out a bottle of stout and takes a long swig from the bottle. He closes his eyes and waits for the liquer to loosen his nerves. &quot;Strange&quot; He thinks.<br>
&quot;I have never known such fear. Not even when I was fighting that craig by myself in FM.&quot;<br>
Having steadied his nerves he ventures into the forest, towards the hidden danger.<br>
Sneaking among the trees, in a very unbarbarian like way, he starts to hear hushed voices in a distinctly foreign tongue.<br>
He sits down, closes his eyes, and focuses on hearing the voices.<br>
He has basic knowledge of all the languages he's ever heard, knowing that the knowledge will some day become handy. <br>
Not like back in the old days, when he was adventuring around<br>
LOIO and an obnoxious halfling thought he could get away with insulting a barbarian by using the halfling language. Which had proven unwise, for this particular barbarian knew enough of the halfling language to get rather angry.<br>
He knows that some day his language skills could be used for something important.<br>
But this particular language is really hard for Khaldorn to comprehend.<br>
He tries instead to catch a glimpse of the beings using the unfamiliar language. He sees small forms, hard to make out in the dark. Judging by the fluid, elegant motions they must be....ElVES....no thats not the elven language....DARK ELVES....<br>
Knowing now which language to focus on, Khaldorn can now understand several words, and each one makes the look on his face turn ever more grim.<br>
Among the words he catches are:<br>
...dark assasins........soon........Phreezin.......dead.......Sphere<br>
.....Donal.........fake crown............mindcontrol....<br>
<br>
Having not fully comprehended the sinister prospect of his encounter, hes decides to quickly scribble down the words and heads back for the camp.<br>
Checking several times for followers he sneaks back to the camp and breathes a sigh of relief as he rouses his companions, wanting to contact the arch druid Aeaden, Chisajr or even Nellen.....someone he can trust within the guild. hurriedly the band packs their stuff for travel. This being done very fast, as they were ready to leave at short notice knowing the danger of the area for young adventurers.  <br>
barely audibly, Canute bestows sow first upon Cogito then himself. But when he turns to grant the spirit of wolf on Khaldorn, the silence is broken by a loud &quot;TWANG&quot;.<br>
Out of the darkness, at incredible speed sails a sheaf arrow and lodges itself in Khaldorns left thigh.<br>
Instead of screaming, he pulls out his large 2 handed hammer and at the same time gives the crucial note to Canute, demanding that Canute brings it to an officer of the Sphere of Honour. Knowing that further discussion and any expression of feelings about leaving Khaldorn behind will only waste precious time, the two youngsters scampers off into the darkness to the sound of Khaldorns probably final....&quot;CHARGE!!!......&quot;<br>
 <p>       "Cogito ergo sum -
    I think therefore I am"
          Rene Descartes
