   Inhaling deeply I relax as the cool air flows into my lungs. Mumbling an almost silent prayer of thanks, &quot;Thank you Tunaare oh how I love your nature.&quot;<br>
     I hunted alone in the dark of the night using my harmony spell to make things relaxed and unrushed, when I felt the winds change slightly. Sure enough as I looked up I saw a man named Cogito running towards the East Commens and Freeport area. People always thought levitate was untrackable and silent but if you not what to look for it was actually louder and easier to track then if you were on the ground. Thats when I realized something was not quite right, the look on Cogito's face was one of extreme unease and a little terror. I wondered why he was in such a hurry and thats when I noticed that something felt very wrong, Nature's night was somehow corrupted their was a small sense of evil in the air. <br>
<br>
   Silently I followed Cogito wandering over WC when I realized he was heading east but not in a direct route, it was a route one would use say if they did not want to be followed and as I began to look for signs of other followers, I realized their was much more to this then at what I first thught. by the time we entered EC I was sure of it two Dark Elf Shadow Knights, were tracking him with relatively apparent ease. They had to be Shadow Knights for they were very good and I almost missed their signs of being their at all. surely Cogito could not know he was being tracked, but the look of unease and terror, he sensed it in the air also the wrongness of it. The Dark Elves were disturbing the peace of the night that alone was enough for me to take pity and spare some time to help this man. I sent my words softly along the wind almost as if they were the wind itself.<br>
<br>
   &quot; Stop friend their are DE's tracking you, if you wish to be free of them double back and...&quot;  I directed him along a route that would eventually bring the DE's back around and they would cross above and in front of me as they were tracking his path. It took a good 10 minutes for him to run the route and I could tell he was getting anxious as I dared not talk to him now because the DE's were closing on him, but he stuck to the route and I thanked Tunaare for the man's courage. As the DE's came close behind I concentrated on the essence of the air and the air where they wuld be silently encanting the words to invoke lightning the air grew charged and as I finished the DE's crossed into the air as two Flashes of light lit up the sky and struck the elves to the ground. One did not rise, as the inevitable thunderous explosion rocked the silence of the night.<br>
<br>
    The other rose and limped toward me with a confidence in his eye's that frightened me for in those eyes I knew he was hurt but I aslo knew that he was very skilled at what he did. As he approached me I panicked a little because I knew he was my better. I casted root and snare, but to no effect his steady unyeilding gait kept coming torwards me.<br>
    The ensuing battle was the a fight for my survival as my sword rang against his and my whip utterly useless for he had cut it in half when I had meant to trip him. Steel clashed against steel and I was growing fatigued yet he seemed only to become more aggressive, I felt a slash upon my shoulder and fell to my knee's here it would end. and as the Shadow Knight brought his sword forward at my head a look of shock suddendly bloomed on his face and he fell next to me silent. Looking at his back there was an arrow shaft, almost expertly shot that probably tipped the heart as it went through the unguarded are of his back, causing the heart to burst. I looked up and there was Cogito...<br>
   &quot; Friend my debt is paid, you saved me for I would have never made freeport, and thus I have returned the favor.&quot; His eye's narrowed,<br>
   &quot; You are Sphere are you not?&quot;<br>
   &quot; Aye that I am brother.&quot;<br>
   &quot; Luck could not be that kind, are you an officer brother of the forest?&quot;<br>
   &quot;Alas, I am not, Maychance I can yet help you.&quot; He pulled out a note and showed it to me and ass I read it, my heart saddened for it implied of things I did not want to acknowledge.<br>
   &quot;Cogito surely you are not the single bearer of this message?&quot;<br>
   &quot;No their is one other though he is probably in more danger then I for he has no help that I know of.&quot;<br>
   &quot; Let us copy this letter then and I too will bear it to where it needs go.&quot;<br>
   &quot; That's an excellent idea brother of the forest.&quot;<br>
and so we copied the notes as I bid him good bye I was floundering through the DE corpses and called out to him to wait. <br>
   &quot; I know not well enough the lit of the DE tounge to read these letters perhaps you...&quot; I let the question hang in the air.<br>
   &quot; Nor I sire.&quot;<br>
   &quot; The assains had these letters on them they probably contain information that would be helpful to Phreezin or Rhaps, surely they can find someone to cipher the lit well enough to maybe give them an advantage over their situation.&quot; <br>
   &quot; Carry this with you also, it may be of great import.&quot;<br>
 Thus we parted our ways and went seperately, at least now I thought their is a messenger they don't know about and hopefully all 3 of us survive this role fate has cast us in.<br>
<br>
