The broken body of Khaldorn stirs slightly, alive but barely.<br>
He lies still to avoid another wash of pain.<br>
Still unbearable pain. Hoping luck has smiled upon him, he looks to see if the enemy has left him for dead.<br>
Another wash of pain, and this time a moan escapes his bloody lips as he passes out. <br>
&quot;Sir!!&quot;, &quot;Hes still alive&quot; an eager young dark elf shouts.<br>
&quot;Too bad for him.&quot; says platoon leader Zealen.<br>
&quot;Chain him and heal him up so he can survive the trek back to the castle. That Sphere scum will be tortured for information and then made an unwilling servant in unlife&quot; <br>
Zealen smiles evilly. The master likes to test his new spells on barbarians. There must be a decent reward for bringing a seasoned warrior. <br>
&quot;you take my mount&quot; Zealen says to the young DE &quot;and bring the barb to the castle. Then have them send 2 platoons. We must catch his companions before they can alert the Sphere. We dont know what they know and they might ruin the masters plan.&quot;<br>
  <p>       "Cogito ergo sum -
    I think therefore I am"
          Rene Descartes
 <br>
<br> I wish you eternal buffs and endless streams of xp 
