<br>
As he practiced his skills a bard approaches him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Art thou named Iaein?&quot;, he asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I have a message for thee&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you good minstrel&quot;. He handed the minstrel a gold piece for his troubles and before he could even thank him, the minstel was out of sight. &quot;Must be amazing to be able to travel at such speeds&quot;, he thought to himself.<br>
<br>
He broke the seal on the parchment and began reading.....<br>
<br>
&quot;My brother Iaein. I hope this letter finds you well. My journeys have been interesting and I have seen many wonderous things. I have missed you and my homeland very much. <br>
<br>
I am writing this letter as I have heard that there have been some disturbing events happenning in Norrath. I am hoping you can give me some information about them. I hear that the Sphere of Honour is in danger and that some of the members have been attacked or killed. I hope this is not so. Things seemed so peaceful when I left. I need to know exactly what has occurred and who is responsible. Rumor has it that Rhapsodey for one has been injured or killed. I need to know if she is safe. I also have heard that it is her royal family that is the source of all the conflict. If it is true that danger is about, I shall journey back and help Sphere become victorious against this tyrant. We will amass as great an army as we have ever had and destroy any that threaten the guild.<br>
<br>
Please get word back to me as soon as you can. I will send a messenger to you at nightfall with a response.<br>
<br>
Be safe my brother. <br>
<br>
With love and honour,<br>
Your brother &quot;<br>
<br>
Iaein wipes the tears from his eyes. It seems forever since he had heard from his brother and is very happy to know that he is alive and well. He can only wonder what adventures his brother has seen and can hardly wait until he can hear more about it. But his task is clear. He must seek out somone in Sphere of Honour and find out if these rumors are true.<br>
<br>
Iaein folds the parchment up and puts it in his backpack, a gift from his brother. He eagerly searches for a druid that can give him sow. Finding one in the middle of the teleport structure he heads to South Karana, a place he has seen many members of the Sphere in recent times. Being an enchanter of the 9th circle his journey is not without peril. He heads to South Karana and the Aviak Village that he has seen Sphere members fighting in.<br>
<br>
&quot;I shall be safe enough with Sow I am sure&quot;<br>
<br>
Iaein heads for South Karana......<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
