<br>
“What are your plans, Dark elf, why were you  holding one of my brothers captive”<br>
<br>
Her attention on the Dark elf in front of her she does not notice the pouch Zalor’s  belt open up and a ring myteriously rises out of it before it vanishes.  <br>
<br>
“why should I tell you anything barbarian,?” the wounded dark elf gasps out. “ You could not understand it anyways, as limited as your brain is”.  With that the Dark elf Spat in Maith’s face.<br>
<br>
With a growl Maith pulls a knife from her belt and places the blade at the Dark Elf’s throat.  “ oh you will talk Scum, believe me before Im done you will talk..” <br>
<br>
Just then the sound of chanting reaches her ears,  A spellcaster.  Before she could recact the earth beneath her feet surges upwards and holds entraps her legs.  As she struggles against the spell she hears another spell start up.  As Maith turned her body to look in that direction, the spell ended and a burst of pure force slammed into her captive and sent her flying out of Maith’s grasp and into a tree.  The Dark elf slumps bonelessly to the ground her body crushed by the force of the spell and the impact with the tree.  <br>
<br>
Maith finally gets turned enough to see another dark elf standing some distance away.  She is dressed in leather armor, and wielding a staff and a strangly glowing shield.  <br>
<br>
“Its nothing personal Barbarian,  she had nothing more to tell you I just saved you the trouble of killing you.”<br>
<br>
Maith readies her warbow and is able to twist her upper body enough to get off a shot.  The arrow shoots towards the dark elf and shatters upon striking her torso.<br>
<br>
“That was pointless” the dark elf says “did you truly think I would reveal myself without bringing up my defenses? After all your reputation preceeds you.  Still I guess its no point in talking to you any further so I will take my leave.  Don’t worry the root spell will wear off in a few minutes.”<br>
<br>
With that the dark elf steps behind a tree and moments later there is the flash of  a teleportation spell being activated.  <br>
<br>
Maith curses.<br>
<br>
Far away from rathe mountains in a secluded vale on the continent of Kunark, the Dark appears.  She then moves away from the mighty combine structure so she can have a little privacy.  <br>
<br>
Pulling the ring she lifted from Zalor she peers at it intensly.  “Hmm”.she muses aloud “I don’t recognize this signet.  It does not match any used by either the great houses or by the dead.  If there is a new faction rising in Neriak then I should inform the master at the tower if the Spurned.” <br>
<br>
She goes to put the ring in her pocket and stops. “ and yet it this group is targeting the Sphere, then there is another I should inform,  If her money is good that is”<br>
<br>
She laughs softly  and calling once again her powers, Fades from view.<br>
