Ruddy Torchlight flickers and casts shadows around a small round room.  There are windows in the room that revealing not the sun and the sky but a ceiling of Dark stone.  A circular table with a few chairs took up the middle of the room, and in the Center of the table a small crystal Globe set on a pile of cushions.   An Elderly Teir'Dal sat in one of the Chairs gazing down upon the globe which was currently giving off a pale blue glow the face of a certain Teir’Dal Wizard can be seen in the globe.<br>
<br>
“ and so that is all I know” <br>
<br>
 The elderly Teir’Dal spoke “It is good that you brought this to my attention my child.  If there is a plot in motion by and unknown agent then we should do our best to make sure we are prepared in case some tries to involve in it without our knowledge.  I will make sure you are rewarded when the time come.”<br>
<br>
“Thank you Elder”, said the Wizard<br>
<br>
 “As for the signet ring I think you should send It to me so we at the tower can start our investigation”<br>
<br>
“Aye Elder I am sending it through now”<br>
<br>
The sphere glows a bit brighter as a globe of light detaches itself and floats down to the table.  The light vanished to reveal the ring.<br>
<br>
“Thank you my child.  Now we will handle the investigation from here.  Forget about what you saw in the Mountains of Rathe and speak of this to no one.  Do you understand?”<br>
<br>
“Yes Elder I understand”<br>
<br>
“Good I will contact you again if I need you for anything.” the Teir”dal waves his hand as the connection is cut off, the globe dims and then goes out.   As he reaches down to pick up the ring a voice comes from the shadows.<br>
<br>
“Do you think she suspects?”<br>
<br>
“No I don’t think so” the elder says, as his features melt away revealing a much younger elf.  “She has been gone for many years, why should she suspect that her teacher has been removed from his position.”<br>
<br>
“It was still a risk to do in the old master”<br>
<br>
“A risk that needed to be taken, the old one was too “noble” for his own good.”  The imposter sneers “ he could have caused problems. “<br>
<br>
“However”, he muses “I think we should keep an eye on his protégé I’m not sure some of his bad traits did not rub of on her.  We must make sure she does not talk.  Assign some men to follow here and if she tries to talk about this to anyone have them kill her immediatley”<br>
<br>
“It will be done” with that a figure in the back of the room turns and leaves.<br>
