&quot;Hmmm, this is grave news indeed. Has anything happenned to you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Let them just try. I have been readying myself in the event of any foul play. I have not been attacked but I do sense something. Sometimes I feel like I am being watched. However if someone does wish to meet my blade, I am surely ready. Thou art a bit young to be out this far. You came here just to find me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I was sent to seek out any Sphere members that can confirm what has been happenning. It appears that these rumors are true and I must get word out quickly&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sent? By whom?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I can't say right now, but I am sure you will know soon. I can assure you that help will be on its way as soon as I send my message.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thou art being a bit mysterious, but you do seem kind and trusting. Is there anything I can help you with?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, thank you M'lady. I must journey back to North Karana. A messenger is coming at nightfall and I must hurry back to meet him. Might I get a Sow from you and possibly invisibility? This is a dangerous area and it will make my journey much safer.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I will do better than that.&quot; Lyena casts a spell and Iaeain is given the Spirit of the Wolf. Then she casts another and the two disappear. As the two vanish a dark elf appears, obviously he had been invisible and was listening to their conversation.<br>
<br>
&quot;So, someone wants to help the Sphere. Those fools have no idea of the danger they are in&quot; His sinister laugh can be heard all over the Aviak Village. &quot;Soon they will learn just how grave their situation is, very soon. But still I must get to North Karana and find out who this person is.&quot; He calls to his companion who was waiting nearby. Come my speedy friend. We must away to North Karana&quot; As his companion starts singing the two disappear in a flash of blue light.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/uiaein.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iaein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(1/7/02 1:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Dangers</span><hr size=1> Iaein and Lyena appear at the druid ring in North Karana. <br>
<br>
&quot;Well here you are my young enchanter friend. A bit faster than SOW wouldn't you say?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes it is, lots faster. And since nighttime is almost here I will have just enough time to write my message before the messenger arrives.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Where are you supposed to meet the messenger?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;At the Wizard Teleport. That is where he first gave me the original message. I was told in that note that he would return later that night for my response&quot;<br>
<br>
As Iaein finished speaking a black wolf started towards him.<br>
<br>
&quot;LOOK OUT&quot;, Lyena said, &quot;If he attacks you the druids and treants will most surely kill you!&quot;<br>
<br>
Since Iaein had had SOW cast upon him he was able to quickly run away before the wolf could attack him. He started running west and Lyena quickly followed him. Once he was safely away from the ring he stopped and started to cast a spell. It was a spell that he had always kept memorized as it had saved him many times in the past. Iaeain casted his spell on the approaching wolf. As soon as the spell was cast the wolf started walking away, completely ignoring his previous prey.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can only assume that was the mum blur spell&quot;, Lyena said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes M'lady. I knew you did not want to harm an animal and neither did I. The easiest way to prevent a conflict was to wipe the animal's memory. Now I need to hurry to the guards at the stone bridge. That is the safest place for me to write my message and close to where the messenger is supposed to meet me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I would like to go with you and make sure you are safe.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you M'lady. You are very kind and I would enjoy your escort&quot;<br>
<br>
The two head for the North Karana bridge.<br>
<br>
Back in South Karana, the dark elf and bard are nearing the South Karana bridge. <br>
<br>
&quot;Quickly my friend. We must get to North Karana and find out who this person is. We do not need any intruders helping The Sphere. Anyone who tries will share the same fate.&quot;, the dark elf exclaimed.<br>
<br>
&quot;We are almost there now Sir. I can see the bridge ahead.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;As soon as we hit the border of North Karana play the invisibility song. I do not wish to be noticed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;As you wish Sir. I will do it now.&quot; As the bard starts playing his song the two fade away. They cross into North Karana just as they notice Iaein and Lyena approaching the bridge.<br>
<br>
Iaein sits down and scribes the message. When he is finished he rolls it up and seals it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Come, we must be at the wizard portal when he arrives. He is due here anytime now.&quot; Iaein pauses to admire the beautiful North Karana sunset and then hurries to the pillars. Lyena follows him not noticing that they are not alone.<br>
<br>
When they get to the bridge they notice a very fast bard approaching from the West.<br>
<br>
&quot;Is this him? He certainly looks like a messenger.&quot;, Lyena said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes it is. He is the same one that gave me the first message.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hail Iaein. I was told to get a message from you. Dost thou have one to send?&quot;<br>
<br>
Iaein gives the message to the bard. &quot;Aye, please deliver this as fast as you can&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I shall Sire. Oh and no payment is necessary. I have been already paid to deliver this message. Good day Sire and M'lady&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Follow him&quot;, whispered the dark elf to the bard. &quot;I want to know where he is headed&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Sir&quot;, the bard replied.<br>
<br>
As the messenger runs off, the dark elf and bard follow him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well Iaein&quot;, Lyena said, &quot;your message is on its way. Do you need any further assistance?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I could use some buffs and another Sow if you don't mind&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not at all. It will be my pleasure&quot; Lyena casts the spells on Iaein. &quot;Now I must head back to my guild. I need to find out if anything else is happenning. I will return here soon to see if you have any news. Be well Iaein.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Fare thee well M'lady. Thank you for all your help. I hope I will be able to help you sometime.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Was my pleasure and as soon as you can cast Breeze, I will most certainly take you up on that offer. Oh, we have not properly met. My name is Lyena and I am at your service if you should ever need help. Was good meeting you. I shall see you soon.&quot; Lyena casts a spell and vanishes.<br>
<br>
&quot;It must be wonderful to be able to teleport like that. I am sure it beats walking. Hmmm, I better stay close to the bridge in case my brother needs my further&quot;, he thinks to himself. &quot;I hope everything will be ok&quot;<br>
<br>
Iaein returns to practicing his spells. &quot;I wonder if I can become a member of The Sphere of Honour someday. That would really be something. I will have to ask Lyena about it when I see her again.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/uiaein.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iaein</A> at: 1/7/02 1:47:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/uvaljeanesbdk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valjeanesbdk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brother of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#330000>(1/7/02 11:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Outlawed</span><hr size=1> Far to the north in the city of Halas Khaldorn is recovering<br>
from his wounds and the evil poisons from dark elf weapons.<br>
He remembers that Reoki.... a great shaman and a member of the Sphere briefly stopped by. During the brief visit Reoki had used some powerful curative spells on him, thus probably saving his life. The fever has lost its grip on him and he is quickly returning to his former strength. <br>
He has gotten a few lessons in dark elf, and the conversation he overheard part of in Rathe Mntns is making more sense to him now.<br>
Apparently the secret master of the dark elves he encountered, has succeded in conjuring a mind-controlling item which bears close resemblance to the crown belonging to the elven king.<br>
Whether this item controls the king or Donal or even both is unknown.<br>
Khaldorn is also convinced that the conflict between Phreezin and Donal is not without some influence from this item. Whether the reason is to make the Sphere fight among themselves or whether it is targeted at Phreezin for some reason, Khaldorn can only speculate. <br>
This more comprehensive record of his experience has been written down and copied, and sent to all leaders and officers of the Sphere. <br>
As Khaldorn sits there...quietly thinking all the events through, Canute storms into the room. <br>
&quot;Khaldorn. Khaldorn you must pack you things and get ready for travel.&quot; Canute almost shouts.<br>
&quot;What?!?! why?!!?&quot; Khaldorn answer, already heeding the shamans request.<br>
&quot;The..the elven king has outlawed all members of the Sphere. And he will also outlaw any friends of the Sphere.&quot; Canute states, looking as if he havent realised the graveness of the news till now.<br>
&quot;Hes has put a bounty on the heads of all Sphere members, and has already assembled a small army to send against us.&quot;<br>
&quot;His reasons are that we kidnap and corrupt people, and the daughter of Donal being one of them. There are other mad accusations, but I dont remember them right now.&quot;<br>
&quot;We are to travel to freeport and meet with other Sphere members. <br>
We can only trust other Sphere members right now, anyone else is a potential enemy. Many will hunt us for the bounty.&quot;<br>
Having now gathered all his belongings, Khaldorn follows Canute outside. The two set off for Freeport.<br>
Many eyes following them..... <br>
   <p>       "Cogito ergo sum -
    I think therefore I am"
          Rene Descartes
 <br>
<br> I wish you eternal buffs and endless streams of xp 
<br>Valjean a.k.a. 
Khaldorn Wyrmguard 35 war, Canute 20 shammy and Cogito 12 wizzy
<br>Proud and loyal members of the Sphere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sornwolf>Sorn Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#330000>(1/8/02 9:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Outlawed</span><hr size=1> In the Court Of Donal Heartsinger<br>
<br>
A messenger enters and approaches Donal Kneeling before him.  My Lord I bring messages pertaining to your Daughter,  Your agents have lost her in the plains of South Karanna near the paw camps.  They Believe that she may have been killed by the paw gnolls and her body eaten.<br>
<br>
Donal:  WHAT.  Send a unit of loyal rangers to search for her  body immediately.  They are not  to return without proof of her death.<br>
<br>
the Messenger leaves quickly with his new mission.<br>
<br>
Seconds later.  as a shadow detaches from the wall and Donal stares blindly at the door that the messenger just left buy.  <br>
<br>
Shadow:&quot; Humm this could present a problem if  that stupid  child got herself killed  by the Gnolls and we cannot recover the body.  This will severally hampers are efforts to bring the High Elf Prince under our sway.  Hummm Mazak have several of agents begin a search through  the local villages for a girl that closely matches the Donal Child we may have to preceded to an alternate plan.<br>
<br>
A warrior Dark Elf appears before Donal:<br>
Mazak:  But Dread Lord wont the High Elf Enchanters notice this when they test her to see if she is actually Donals daughter.  My understanding was that this would only work with the actual child.&quot;   <br>
<br>
Shadow:&quot;  yes we will have to find someway around this situation.  At this time put all effort to finding her and finding a possible replacement&quot;<br>
<br>
Mazak:  Yes Dread Lord you wish will be completed or we will Die Trying.<br>
Mazak quickly departs from the audience chamber<br>
<br>
<br>
Shadow turning to the immobile Donal:  Well my puppet what is your Daughter doing.  I have a hard time believing after all the things she has already done that she would fall to simple Paw Gnolls.  HUMMMMMM  she is much more  resourcefully than any of my advisor could have envisioned.  I will definatly have to break her myself.  This will be fun forming her to my will.<br>
<br>
The Shadow paces back and  Forth before Donals unseeing eyes.<br>
<br>
Shadow:  Enough I think I will go speak to your wife I may be able to get some useful info from her.  <br>
<br>
With that the Shadow leaves through a hidden side door Leaving Donal sitting in his chair.<br>
<br>
A silent tear forms at the  corner of Donals eye and runs down his immobile face<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bsphereofhonour58352.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sornwolf>Sorn Wolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Sphere</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#330000>(1/8/02 9:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fsphereofhonour58352frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Outlawed</span><hr size=1> Meanwhile Outside The Donal Mansion in the Kelathin forest.<br>
<br>
A lone Female Dark Elf stands silently hidden in the Shadows watching the comming and going of the Mansion.  Her Dark blue eyes not missing a thing not even the comming and goings of the Dark elves who are hidden by Invisibility spells.  <br>
<br>
Her Keen magical senses detect the opening of a gate near her location as she turns to look around she suddenly gasps as she doubles over Wrapping her arms around her stomach in pain.  She  quickly reaches into one of her pouches and pulls out a bottle with shakcing hands she opens the vial  and quickly drinks its contents.  Having no more than finished the contents of the bottle her senses detect motion comming from the forest.  As she watches a specter ghost quietly from behind a tree and glides over her silently.  Her skin raising in goose bumps at the close proximety of the specter.  Shortly after the first one passes more of them appear in the forest moving toward the mansion.  By the time the last one has passed she has counted 40 specters moving into the Mansion.  As she watches the last one pass through the mansion walls the pain her stomach passes and she quickly stands and moves off into the forest.<br>
<br>
Shortly she arrives at her destination a small  cave hidden in the side of a hill behind some ancient oak trees.  With the knowledge of some one who has been here before she careful climbs into the small cave avoiding  the traps that have been set within the cave.  She crawls back into the cave to a small camp set within.  STanding she takes a pen parchement and an ink well from the bag placed against the wall.  She carefully pens the words,&quot; The enemy has come as you expected.  The Heartsinger family is no more the last living member will die shortly at my hands.  We live for the one we die for the Honour of our king. May the Goddess protect us in our Mission&quot;  After completing the Message she rolls it carefully and places it in a metal tube.  Turning she takes a messnger Falcon from a perch and secures the message to his leg. Walking to the smoke vent in the ceiling of the cave she removes the hood from the Falcon and tosses him through the hole with the command to go home.  <br>
<br>
This done she turns to her bags and begins to unpack the making of a meal.  Knowing that if she fail and is discovered before everything is in place that this may be the last meal she may ever eat.<br>
